description: Creates a new custom endpoint and associates it with an Amazon Neptune DB cluster.

parameters.name: DBClusterIdentifier
parameters.description: The DB cluster identifier of the DB cluster associated with the endpoint. This parameter is stored as a lowercase string.

parameters.name: DBClusterEndpointIdentifier
parameters.description: The identifier to use for the new endpoint. This parameter is stored as a lowercase string.

parameters.name: EndpointType
parameters.description: The type of the endpoint. One of: READER, WRITER, ANY.

parameters.name: StaticMembers
parameters.description: List of DB instance identifiers that are part of the custom endpoint group. (string) ---

parameters.name: ExcludedMembers
parameters.description: List of DB instance identifiers that aren't part of the custom endpoint group. All other eligible instances are reachable through the custom endpoint. Only relevant if the list of static members is empty. (string) ---

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: The tags to be assigned to the Amazon Neptune resource. (dict) --- Metadata assigned to an Amazon Neptune resource consisting of a key-value pair. Key (string) --- A key is the required name of the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 128 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with aws: or rds:. The string can only contain the set of Unicode letters, digits, white-space, --_', --.', --/', --=', --+', ---' (Java regex: '^([\p{L}\p{Z}\p{N}_.:/=+\-]*)$'). Value (string) --- A value is the optional value of the tag. The string value can be from 1 to 256 Unicode characters in length and can't be prefixed with aws: or rds:. The string can only contain the set of Unicode letters, digits, white-space, --_', --.', --/', --=', --+', ---' (Java regex: '^([\p{L}\p{Z}\p{N}_.:/=+\-]*)$').
